  "prompt": "Are there legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several legal frameworks designed to combat money laundering:\n\n1. International Level\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n\n2. United States\n- Bank Secrecy Act (BSA)\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) regulations\n- USA PATRIOT Act\n\n3. European Union\n- Anti-Money Laundering Directives\n- Comprehensive regulatory frameworks\n- Mandatory reporting requirements\n\n4. Key Prevention Mechanisms\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) procedures\n- Suspicious transaction reporting\n- Customer due diligence\n- Enhanced financial institution monitoring\n\n5. Penalties\n- Significant financial penalties\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Asset seizure\n- Potential imprisonment\n\n6. Enforcement Agencies\n- Financial Crimes Enforcement Network (FinCEN)\n- Internal Revenue Service\n- National financial intelligence units\n\nThese frameworks aim to detect, prevent, and prosecute money laundering activities through comprehensive legal and regulatory approaches.\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any specific aspect of money laundering legal frameworks?",
